<subSubSection id="713CC019B643F2B0D26DA3D8991C4704" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="notes">
<paragraph id="1545D421CA49C0B3802AF8B21AECB17B" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC1AA36F3C9C3E055718E412FDB88C63" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
The protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="3F206FFFC3600D2E18F262BC803A49B8" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium diffusum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="diffusum">
<emphasis id="6F3D5CD99E145F513D95CA9E111C2380" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Eritrichium diffusum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="2857A0E0AF9915A6B3F8475B1F8A0460" author="Philippi, RA" journalOrPublisher="Linnaea" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 308" refId="B36" refString="Philippi, RA, 1864. Plantarum novarum Chilensium. Linnaea 33: 1 - 308" title="Plantarum novarum Chilensium." volume="33" year="1864">Philippi 1864</bibRefCitation>
) includes a direct reference to a collection made by Herman Volckmann in Coquimbo, Chile. 
<bibRefCitation id="EAC5A9B4EF0727359A63ED3C8D49A6E7" author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">Johnston (1927)</bibRefCitation>
referred to a specimen lodged at SGO as the 
<normalizedToken id="345B21B46BF5CEAEE816A22D2FA460EC" originalValue="“type”">&quot;type&quot;</normalizedToken>
of the name, while 
<bibRefCitation id="2F73B0E6DA6F3598CD98D4A3D3DB4D7D" author="Perez-Moreau, RL" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" refId="B30" refString="Perez-Moreau, RL, 1976. Revision del genero Cryptantha en la Argentina (Boraginaceae). Darwiniana 20(1/2): 155-188." title="Revision del genero Cryptantha en la Argentina (Boraginaceae). Darwiniana 20 (1 / 2): 155 - 188." year="1976">
<normalizedToken id="DF32628D9A2F8771111FC4132BEC1D0D" originalValue="Pérez-Moreau">Perez-Moreau</normalizedToken>
(1976)
</bibRefCitation>
later stated &quot;Chile. Coquimbo: Huanta, 
<normalizedToken id="2AC98EF8B2E299A8AAF77ECF5806C8A6" originalValue="Baños">Banos</normalizedToken>
del Toro, 1860-61, Volckmann (tipo de 
<taxonomicName id="7AB121D02F25F5A1053405E20739CE5D" genus="E." lsidName="E. diffusum" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" rank="species" species="diffusum">
<emphasis id="C689F18A1D0029BAFEC8CD1F71AB7CA0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">E. diffusum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, SGO)&quot;. Despite the statements of these authors, in the general collection at SGO two sheets were found in agreement with the protologue. The specimens match the diagnosis as coined by Philippi. In this framework, the earliest statement made by 
<bibRefCitation id="BACC53CC8BDF59C8F71187A73668E76D" author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">Johnston (1927)</bibRefCitation>
is here interpreted as a first-step lectotypification. In order to narrow this broad designation, the sheet SGO000004064 is here selected as a second-step lectotype.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="36EB1AF0A1414DCA366133C195F35D95" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
<bibRefCitation id="5A17818D47ABC18017406AAD45244FC6" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.162865" author="Philippi, RA" journalOrPublisher="INTA, Buenos Aires" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" refId="B35" refString="Philippi, RA, 1860. Florula Atacamensis seu enumeratio plantarum, quas in itinere per desertum Atacamense. Sumptibus E. Anton. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.162865" title="Florula Atacamensis seu enumeratio plantarum, quas in itinere per desertum Atacamense. Sumptibus E. Anton." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.162865" year="1860">Rudolph A. Philippi (1860)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="A28AD9F811345690A3C18FF2EE202E61" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium micranthum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="micranthum">
<emphasis id="099239A78BCE9B6A9DFE99CFAC52FC31" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Eritrichium micranthum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on a collection he made in 
<normalizedToken id="9F74835EB174E2519079CAB1345FECAF" originalValue="Sandón">Sandon</normalizedToken>
, Chile, with no further reference. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="DFB627327BF8ABD6B78E257909A5901B" author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">Johnston (1927)</bibRefCitation>
, the type element of this species is housed at SGO. 
<bibRefCitation id="76F8BE4645FF7805C2AF15405EE3EE86" author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">
<normalizedToken id="1EEB9033FB80939E68CCDA8A3DBEED6C" originalValue="Johnston’s">Johnston's</normalizedToken>
(1927)
</bibRefCitation>
statement is here interpreted as a first-step lectotype designation since two sheets in agreement with the protologue and annotated by Philippi as &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="7B8D5797A217D8CB1847BDD3DF70DCAD" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium micranthum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="micranthum">Eritrichium micranthum</taxonomicName>
&quot; were found at SGO. The specimens involved match the protologue and, thus, the designation of 
<bibRefCitation id="C44CCF2697849C4A595BBD05E35CE078" author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">Johnston (1927)</bibRefCitation>
is here narrowed by selecting the sheet SGO000004107 as a second step-lectotype.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A9C6FB7757ABEF6E997A172419E2A1E4" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
In the protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="78B4BE4D503380BA59E563EFBFAB5EB1" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cryptantha famatinae" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="famatinae">
<emphasis id="B44A1168051ADA8316D80B2A34C6E3C8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Cryptantha famatinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="57EA08DE40964868E3A68258C5506134" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/fedr.19240200617" author="Brand, A" journalOrPublisher="Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="317 - 320" refId="B3" refString="Brand, A, 1924. Decas specierum novarum quinta. Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis 20 (6-21): 317 - 320, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/fedr.19240200617" title="Decas specierum novarum quinta." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/fedr.19240200617" volume="20" year="1924">Brand (1924)</bibRefCitation>
cited a collection made by Georg H. E. W. Hieronymus and Gustav Niederlein in the province of La Rioja, Argentina. No original collections could be traced at B, where Brand worked (
<bibRefCitation id="ABF29256972CDCF7669325530AF6D32B" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48631" author="Stafleu, FA" journalOrPublisher="Anales del Museo Buenos Aires" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" refId="B46" refString="Stafleu, FA, Cowan, RS, 1976. Taxonomic Literature Vol. 1, a Selective Guide to Botanical Publications and Collections with Dates, Commentaries and Types, ed. 2. Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema, Utrecht. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48631" title="Taxonomic Literature Vol. 1, a Selective Guide to Botanical Publications and Collections with Dates, Commentaries and Types, ed. 2. Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema, Utrecht." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48631" year="1976">Stafleu and Cowan 1976</bibRefCitation>
), but duplicates of Hieronymus and 
<normalizedToken id="F028FE825E99D4787D86A667CB986692" originalValue="Niederlein’s">Niederlein's</normalizedToken>
collection were located at CORD and GH. These sheets agree with the diagnosis and cited locality found in the protologue. Thus, the sheet CORD00003765 is here selected as lectotype of the name.
</paragraph>
